  <title>Gio.OutputStream::splice_async</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function vfunc_splice_async(source: Gio.InputStream, flags: Gio.OutputStreamSpliceFlags, io_priority: Number, cancellable: Gio.Cancellable, callback: Gio.AsyncReadyCallback): void {
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Splices a stream asynchronously.
When the operation is finished <code>callback</code> will be called.
You can then call <link xref="Gio.OutputStream.splice_finish"/> to get the
result of the operation.</p>  <p>For the synchronous, blocking version of this function, see
<link xref="Gio.OutputStream.splice"/>.</p>

<terms>
<item>
<title><code>source</code></title>
  <p>a <link xref="Gio.InputStream"/>.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>flags</code></title>
  <p>a set of <link xref="Gio.OutputStreamSpliceFlags"/>.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>io_priority</code></title>
  <p>the io priority of the request.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>cancellable</code></title>
  <p>optional <link xref="Gio.Cancellable"/> object, <code>null</code> to ignore.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>callback</code></title>
  <p>a <link xref="Gio.AsyncReadyCallback"/>.</p>
</item>
</terms>

